# API routes (server output)

- Astro may probe **`GET`** during the build. If only **`POST`** is exported, the build can warn. Prefer adding a small **`GET`** that returns **405** + `Allow: POST` for non-GET semantics, or document intentional behavior.
- This project deploys with a **Node server** (`@astrojs/node`). **Pure static hosting** (no Node) cannot execute **`POST`** handlers; use the documented Docker/LXC setup or another serverless/SSR host—see project skill `astro-static-forms`.

Keep handlers minimal; validate input server-side; never log secrets.
